  <fr:mainmatter>
    <html:p>A <html:em>computation path</html:em> is defined to be a finite <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00BV.xml" title="Elementary event structures" addr="jms-00BV" type="local">elementary</fr:link> <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00BN.xml" title="Event structure" addr="jms-00BN" type="local">event structure</fr:link>; we define the category of computation paths to be the full subcategory of <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00BN.xml" title="Event structure" addr="jms-00BN" type="local">event structures</fr:link> and <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00BR.xml" title="Rigid morphisms of event structures" addr="jms-00BR" type="local">rigid maps</fr:link> spanned by computation paths.</html:p>
  </fr:mainmatter>
