            </fr:date>
            <fr:addr>jms-00BN</fr:addr>
            <fr:route>https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00BN.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Event structure">Event structure</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
            <fr:meta name="source">
              <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/staton-winskel-2010.xml" title="On the expressivity of symmetry in event structures" addr="staton-winskel-2010" type="local">[staton-winskel-2010]</fr:link>
            </fr:meta>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>An <html:em>event structure</html:em> is defined to be triple <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (E,\mathsf {Con}_{E}, \leq _E\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> where <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[E]]></fr:tex> is a partial order of <html:em>events</html:em> partially ordered by the <html:em>causal dependency relation</html:em> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\leq _E]]></fr:tex>, and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {Con}_{E}\subseteq  \mathcal {P}_{\mathit {fin}}{\mathopen {}\left (E\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> specifies when a finite subset of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[E]]></fr:tex> is <html:em>consistent</html:em>, satisfying the following laws:</html:p>
            <html:ol><html:li>every downset of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[E]]></fr:tex> is finite;</html:li>
  <html:li>every singleton set is consistent;</html:li>
  <html:li>any subset of a consistent subset is consistent;</html:li>
  <html:li>for any consistent subset <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x\in \mathsf {Con}_{E}]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[e\leq  e']]></fr:tex> with <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[e'\in  x]]></fr:tex>, we have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x\cup {\mathopen {}\left \{e\right \}\mathclose {}}\in \mathsf {Con}_{E}]]></fr:tex>.</html:li></html:ol>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
