            <fr:title text="Rigid morphisms of event structures">Rigid morphisms of <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00BN.xml" title="Event structure" addr="jms-00BN" type="local">event structures</fr:link></fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
            <fr:meta name="source">
              <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/staton-winskel-2010.xml" title="On the expressivity of symmetry in event structures" addr="staton-winskel-2010" type="local">[staton-winskel-2010]</fr:link>
            </fr:meta>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>A <html:em>rigid morphism</html:em> of <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00BN.xml" title="Event structure" addr="jms-00BN" type="local">event structures</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{E}\xrightarrow {{f}}{E'}]]></fr:tex> is a monotone function on events that preserves finite <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00BO.xml" title="Configurations of an event structure" addr="jms-00BO" type="local">configurations</fr:link> and is <html:em>locally injective</html:em> in the sense that for any finite <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00BO.xml" title="Configurations of an event structure" addr="jms-00BO" type="local">configuration</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x\in \mathcal {C}_{E}^{\mathit {fin}}]]></fr:tex> and events <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[e_1,e_2\in  x]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[fe_1 = fe_2]]></fr:tex>, we have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[e_1=e_2]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
